track.name: Anywhere I Lay My Head
comments: That's a one of a kind singing voice..
This is easily the most amazing song I've heard in a long-ass time.
shortlist for favourite song of all-fucking-time.
Absolutely amazing. One of the best album closers ever, the ending gets me every time.
i love it when the closer is the strongest on the album
Can't stand his voice!
scooby doo best song
i learned to be alone...oh tom!
Nice cover of Scarlett Johansson.

I can't help myself..this song moves me inside so much every time.....and,damn..his voice! and those lyrics! I want the lyric from this song tatooed on my skin!
 " Well I don’t need anybody, because I learned, I learned to be alone
Well I said anywhere, anywhere, anywhere I lay my head, boys
Well I gonna call my home”
Seems that my pockets were filled up with gold.
Wow.
I rarely like anynone's singing performance more than in this song.
Favourite vocal performance on Rain Dogs. fucking shivers
party rock anthem
terrifying
One of the greatest voices ever. [4]
fuck yes, this is the one!
